{{/* User-prompt template for the per-day memory reconciliation pass.
   The system prompt (memoryReconcileSystemPrompt in chat/memory.go)
   sets the schema and durability rules; this template provides the
   inputs.

   Variables:
     .LocalDate — YYYY-MM-DD
     .Weekday   — e.g. "Friday"
     .Daily     — *MemoryDayInput or nil {MoodLabel, DrainedText,
                  ChargedText, GratitudeText, ReflectionText}
     .Entries   — []MemoryDayEntry{Prompt, Body}
     .Writable  — []MemoryView{ID, Category, Content} (may be updated/deleted)
     .Pinned    — []MemoryView (read-only, user-locked)
*/ -}}

# Journal record for {{.Weekday}}, {{.LocalDate}}

{{if .Daily -}}
## Daily check-in
{{if .Daily.MoodLabel}}Mood: {{.Daily.MoodLabel}}
{{end -}}
{{if .Daily.DrainedText}}What drained them: {{.Daily.DrainedText}}
{{end -}}
{{if .Daily.ChargedText}}What charged them: {{.Daily.ChargedText}}
{{end -}}
{{if .Daily.GratitudeText}}Grateful for: {{.Daily.GratitudeText}}
{{end -}}
{{if .Daily.ReflectionText}}Reflection: {{.Daily.ReflectionText}}
{{end}}
{{end -}}
{{if .Entries -}}
## Journal entries
{{range .Entries}}Q: {{.Prompt}}
A: {{.Body}}

{{end}}
{{end -}}
# Existing memories you may UPDATE or DELETE

Reference these by `id` verbatim — never invent an id.
{{if .Writable}}
{{range .Writable -}}
- id={{.ID}} [{{.Category}}] {{.Content}}
{{end}}
{{- else}}
(none yet)
{{end}}
{{if .Pinned -}}
# User-locked memories (read-only)

The user wrote or confirmed these themselves. You must NOT update or
delete them, and you must NOT re-add a fact already covered by one of
them.

{{range .Pinned -}}
- [{{.Category}}] {{.Content}}
{{end}}
{{end -}}

Now emit the JSON object exactly per the schema in the system prompt.
If today's record contains no new durable facts, emit {"operations": []}.
